The paper discusses channel coding in wireless communication systems, specifically focusing on polar codes for control channels in the future 5G standard. This topic falls under the information theory (cs.IT), communication (cs.COMM), and systems and control (cs.SY) categories. The paper also discusses optimizations and tradeoffs related to the implementation of the decoder, which could fall under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and architecture (cs.AR) categories.
